cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper discusses the development and deployment of interactive artificial intelligence-based conversational agents, making it highly relevant to the AI sub-category.
2. cs.CL - The use of deep learning to train the artificial improvisor and generate plausible lines of dialogue makes this paper relevant to the computational linguistics sub-category.
3. cs.HC - The paper explores the interaction between humans and machines in a live performance setting, making it relevant to the human-computer interaction sub-category.
4. cs.LG - The use of deep learning to train the artificial improvisor also makes this paper relevant to the machine learning sub-category.
5. cs.SD - The paper collects anonymous feedback from volunteer performers and audience members to test scientific hypotheses about the perception of humans versus machines, making it relevant to the social and information networks sub-category.
